name: Turtles® Cake I
author: Debbie
summary: Chocolate cake with melted caramels, nuts, and chocolate chips in the middle.
ingredients: 1 (18.25 ounce) package German chocolate cake mix
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Mix cake mix according to package directions
Pour a little less than half of the batter into prepared pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) remove from oven
Melt caramels, margarine, and milk in the microwave on high (takes about 10 minutes), stirring a couple times
Or alternately melt in a sauce pan over medium low heat
Pour melted caramel mixture over cake, sprinkle with pecans, and chocolate chips, and pour remaining cake batter over the top
Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 20 to 35 minutes
